OL,3,CHungary elections: What is at stake,
OL,4,Cand why do they matter?
OL,6,FWords by ITV News Deputy Content
OL,7,FEditor, Georgia Ziebart
OL,9,FHungary's election on Sunday could see
OL,10,Fthe defeat of the European Union's
OL,11,Flongest-serving leader.
OL,13,FA far-right friend of Russian
OL,14,FPresident Vladimir Putin, and a
OL,15,Fstaunch ally of the Trump
OL,16,Fadministration, Hungarian Prime
OL,17,FMinister Viktor Orban is trailing
OL,18,Fbehind in the polls.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1775873035
OL,3,CHungary elections: What is at stake,
OL,4,Cand why do they matter?
OL,6,FIt is an election being closely
OL,7,Fwatched across the globe, and one
OL,8,Fwhich has implications reaching well
OL,9,Fbeyond Budapest.
OL,11,FUS Vice President JD Vance on Tuesday
OL,12,Furged Hungarians to back the populist
OL,13,Fleader, dubbing him a defender of
OL,14,F"Western civilisation", in a visit to
OL,15,Fthe country meant to help push Orban
OL,16,Fover the line.
OL,18,FBut how likely is it that Orban's far-
OL,19,Fright government is defeated, and why
OL,20,Fare these elections so consequential?
OL,21,FITV News explains.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1775873035
OL,3,CHungary elections: What is at stake,
OL,4,Cand why do they matter?
OL,6,FWho is Viktor Orban?
OL,8,FOrban has dominated Hungarian politics
OL,9,Ffor more than two decades, and over
OL,10,Fhis 16-year reign has reshaped the
OL,11,Fcountry into what the European
OL,12,FParliament described as an "electoral
OL,13,Fautocracy".
OL,15,FIn 1988, Orban co-founded his party
OL,16,FFidesz - originally a liberal, anti-
OL,17,Fcommunist youth party. The following
OL,18,Fyear, then a 26-year-old law student,
OL,19,Fhe gave a fiery speech before tens of
OL,20,Fthousands of Hungarians, demanding
OL,21,FSoviet troops leave the country.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1775873035
OL,3,CHungary elections: What is at stake,
OL,4,Cand why do they matter?
OL,6,FHe became one of Europe's youngest
OL,7,Fever prime ministers when he won the
OL,8,Fnational election ten years later at
OL,9,Fthe age of 35.
OL,11,FBut as Hungary's political dynamics
OL,12,Fchanged, and other liberal parties
OL,13,Femerged, Orban began steering Fidesz
OL,14,Ffurther right, transforming the party
OL,15,Finto a vehicle for increasingly
OL,16,Fnationalist conservatism.
OL,18,FHaving lost power, Orban was re-
OL,19,Felected once again in 2010, after
OL,20,Friding the fallout from the 2008
OL,21,Fglobal financial crisis.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1775873035
OL,3,CHungary elections: What is at stake,
OL,4,Cand why do they matter?
OL,6,FFor many observers, this marked a
OL,7,Fturning point in Orban's politics.
OL,8,FWith an overwhelming mandate, Fidesz
OL,9,Fbegan reshaping Hungary by
OL,10,Funilaterally writing a new
OL,11,Fconstitution, re-rigging the electoral
OL,12,Fsystem, and stacking the courts.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1775873035
OL,3,CHungary elections: What is at stake,
OL,4,Cand why do they matter?
OL,6,FIt also marked a significant
OL,7,Ftransformation in public media in
OL,8,FHungary. Orban's party spent billions
OL,9,Fon state-funded communication,
OL,10,Ftransforming public media as well as
OL,11,Fbillboards and adverts into
OL,12,Fmouthpieces for the state. Media
OL,13,Fwatchdog Reporters Without Borders
OL,14,Fcalled Orban a press freedom
OL,15,F"predator".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1775873035
OL,3,CHungary elections: What is at stake,
OL,4,Cand why do they matter?
OL,6,FBut despite global leaders and the EU
OL,7,Fwarning against Orban's actions, his
OL,8,Fsupporters praise him as a defender of
OL,9,FChristian, nationalistic values in the
OL,10,Fface of mass migration and what he
OL,11,Fdescribes as an increasingly
OL,12,Foppressive EU.
OL,14,FSuch values have also led to
OL,15,Fsignificant criticism and concern from
OL,16,Fwithin Hungary - in 2022, one of
OL,17,FOrban's closest associates resigned in
OL,18,Fprotest over what she called a "pure
OL,19,FNazi" speech Orban gave, in which he
OL,20,Frailed against becoming a "mixed race
OL,21,Fsociety".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1775873035
OL,3,CHungary elections: What is at stake,
OL,4,Cand why do they matter?
OL,6,FWhile Orban's anti-migration narrative
OL,7,Fand criticism of liberal values had
OL,8,Flong prompted backlash, his escalating
OL,9,Frhetoric in recent years has sparked
OL,10,Fincreasing outrage throughout Europe
OL,11,Fand from Hungary's opposition.
OL,13,FWhat would Orban losing mean for
OL,14,Fglobal politics?
OL,16,FOrban's government has long been a
OL,17,Fthorn in the side of the European
OL,18,FUnion.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1775873035
OL,3,CHungary elections: What is at stake,
OL,4,Cand why do they matter?
OL,6,FHe has frequently clashed with the
OL,7,Fbloc over press freedom, migration,
OL,8,Fanti-LGBTQ+ legislation and
OL,9,Fcorruption. Most recently, his
OL,10,Fgovernment has prevented EU efforts to
OL,11,Fsupport Ukraine and sanction Russia
OL,12,Fover its full-scale invasion.
OL,14,FThe EU has frozen billions in funding
OL,15,Fto Hungary over concerns the country
OL,16,Fmight put the bloc's budget at risk.
OL,17,FIn return, Orban has campaigned
OL,18,Fheavily against the EU, comparing it
OL,19,Fto the Soviet Union.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30410
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1775873035
OL,3,CHungary elections: What is at stake,
OL,4,Cand why do they matter?
OL,6,F"This election is a momentous one,"
OL,7,FGregoire Roos, Director of the Europe
OL,8,Fand Russia and Eurasia programmes at
OL,9,FChatham House told ITV News.
OL,11,F"It matters because Hungary has become
OL,12,Fa hinge point inside Europe`able to
OL,13,Fshape or block decisions on Ukraine,
OL,14,Fsanctions, and EU policy."
OL,16,FHis rival, Peter Magyar, vowed to
OL,17,Fquickly un-freeze EU payouts if he
OL,18,Fwins the election, and will seek to
OL,19,Fease the years bad blood between the
OL,20,Fbloc and Hungary.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30411
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1775873035
OL,3,CHungary elections: What is at stake,
OL,4,Cand why do they matter?
OL,6,FBut Brussels should not expect an
OL,7,Fimmediate transformation. Magyar has
OL,8,Falready confirmed he would continue to
OL,9,Foppose the EU migration pact, and
OL,10,Fremains wary of Ukraine's potential
OL,11,Faccession to the bloc.
OL,13,F"A defeat of Viktor Orban would not
OL,14,Foverturn the system overnight, but it
OL,15,Fcould ease tensions with Brussels,
OL,16,Funlock EU funds, and make European
OL,17,Fdecision-making more cohesive," Roos
OL,18,Ftold ITV News.
OL,20,FTies with Russia
OL,26,@uD@Xrp
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30412
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1775873035
OL,3,CHungary elections: What is at stake,
OL,4,Cand why do they matter?
OL,6,FWhile further alienating Hungary from
OL,7,FWestern Europe, Orban has cultivated
OL,8,Fclose ties with like-minded leaders
OL,9,Fincluding Russian President Vladimir
OL,10,FPutin.
OL,12,FOrban's other allies in the region
OL,13,Finclude France's Marine Le Pen,
OL,14,FItaly's Matteo Salvini, and Geert
OL,15,FWilders of the Netherlands.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30413
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1775873035
OL,3,CHungary elections: What is at stake,
OL,4,Cand why do they matter?
OL,6,FHis foreign policy at odds with the
OL,7,FWestern consensus has drawn
OL,8,Faccusations that he is acting to
OL,9,Fbenefit Moscow, with some media
OL,10,Freports suggesting Russian secret
OL,11,Fservices were meddling to tip Sunday's
OL,12,Fvote in Orban's favour - something
OL,13,FRussia denies.
OL,15,FOther reports accuse Orban's foreign
OL,16,Fminister of frequently sharing
OL,17,Fsensitive details on closed door EU
OL,18,Fmeetings with his Russian counterpart
OL,19,F- a revelation which Polish prime
OL,20,Fminister Donald Tusk said "shouldn't
OL,21,Fcome as a surprise to anyone."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30414
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1775873035
OL,3,CHungary elections: What is at stake,
OL,4,Cand why do they matter?
OL,6,FIn any case, Orban is broadly seen as
OL,7,FEurope's most Moscow-friendly leader,
OL,8,Fcontinuing to invest in Russian oil
OL,9,Fand gas even as the rest of the EU
OL,10,Fsanction it. The prospect of a change
OL,11,Fof government could recalibrate the
OL,12,Fbalance between Hungary, Russia, and
OL,13,FEurope.
OL,15,FA friend of the Trump administration
OL,17,FMeanwhile, the Trump administration
OL,18,Fhas expressed support for Orban's
OL,19,Fgovernment, with US Vice President JD
OL,20,FVance visiting Budapest last week in a
OL,21,Frare campaigning effort.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30415
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1775873035
OL,3,CHungary elections: What is at stake,
OL,4,Cand why do they matter?
OL,6,FVance slammed Orban critics in the EU
OL,7,Ffor what he called "foreign
OL,8,Finterference" in the election, even as
OL,9,Fhe spoke at campaign rallies to, in
OL,10,Fhis own words, "help as much as I
OL,11,Fpossibly can".
OL,13,FThe visit was officially intended to
OL,14,Fdeepen ties between the US and
OL,15,FHungary, during what Orban has called
OL,16,Fa "golden era" of their relations.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30416
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1775873035
OL,3,CHungary elections: What is at stake,
OL,4,Cand why do they matter?
OL,6,FAmong other similar priorities
OL,7,Fincluding immigration and gender
OL,8,Fideology, the two administrations
OL,9,Fshare an approach towards ending
OL,10,FRussia's war in Ukraine - an approach
OL,11,Fmany analysts say favours Moscow. On
OL,12,FTuesday, Vance claimed the "two
OL,13,Fleaders who have probably done the
OL,14,Fmost to actually end that destructive
OL,15,Fconflict" are Trump and Orban.
OL,26,@tD@\OUwD@IO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30417
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1775873035
OL,3,CHungary elections: What is at stake,
OL,4,Cand why do they matter?
OL,6,F"The election will serve as a Trojan
OL,7,Fhorse for the US National Security
OL,8,FStrategy in Europe and the aggressive
OL,9,Fpolicy of support of the US
OL,10,FAdministration to so-called "patriot"
OL,11,Fmovements across Europe," Roos told
OL,12,FITV News, "Something everyone on the
OL,13,Ffar right, from Le Pen to Farage and
OL,14,Fnow Meloni is willing to politically
OL,15,Fdie for, given how toxic any
OL,16,Fassociation with Trump, Vance and his
OL,17,Faffiliates has become."
OL,26,@rD@]OUrD@eO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30418
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1775873035
OL,3,CHungary elections: What is at stake,
OL,4,Cand why do they matter?
OL,6,FThe US president posted on his Truth
OL,7,FSocial platform: "GET OUT AND VOTE FOR
OL,8,FVIKTOR ORBAN. He is a true friend,
OL,9,Ffighter, and WINNER, and has my
OL,10,FComplete and Total Endorsement. I AM
OL,11,FWITH HIM ALL THE WAY!"
OL,13,FYet Trump's support has not appeared
OL,14,Fto move the needle much in Hungary,
OL,15,Fwith polls still showing only 37% of
OL,16,Frespondents backing Orban, versus 56%
OL,17,Fsupporting the opposing Tisza party.
OL,19,FWhat's the alternative?
OL,26,@oD@ROUpD@Kr`sD@VO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G18/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30419
SC,0019
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1775873035
OL,3,CHungary elections: What is at stake,
OL,4,Cand why do they matter?
OL,6,FHungary's opposition leader, Peter
OL,7,FMagyar, and the leader of the Tisza
OL,8,Fparty, has charted a meteoric rise
OL,9,Fsince bursting into public view in
OL,10,F2024.
OL,12,FBut before emerging as Orban's most
OL,13,Fprominent critic, Magyar spent years
OL,14,Finside the prime minister's own Fidesz
OL,15,Fparty.
OL,17,FOnly two days before the vote, most
OL,18,Fpolls placed Tisza with a double-digit
OL,19,Flead over Fidesz ` a feat no
OL,20,Fopposition force has achieved since
OL,21,FOrban returned to power in 2010.
OL,26,@}D@Drp
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G19/23
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30420
SC,0020
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1775873035
OL,3,CHungary elections: What is at stake,
OL,4,Cand why do they matter?
OL,6,FWhile some of Magyar's supporters are
OL,7,Fwary of his former ties to the ruling
OL,8,Fparty, others believe only someone who
OL,9,Fhas seen Orban's system from the
OL,10,Finside can bring it down.
OL,12,FMagyar's rise has energised a segment
OL,13,Fof Hungarian society which had
OL,14,Fpreviously been disillusioned with
OL,15,Fprevious generations of fragmented and
OL,16,Fineffectual opposition parties, with
OL,17,Fno viable alternative to Orban.
OL,26,@qD@Mrp
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G20/23
