OL,3,CHungary elections: What is at stake,
OL,4,Cand why do they matter?
OL,6,FAnd even if he is well ahead in the
OL,7,Fpolls, the prospect of Magyar actually
OL,8,Fwinning the election remains uncertain
OL,9,Famid a skewed electoral playing field,
OL,10,Fmoulded by Orban over years to create
OL,11,Fan unfair advantage. Under such
OL,12,Fcircumstances, it remains unclear
OL,13,Fwhether Tisza's votes translate into a
OL,14,Freal majority.
OL,16,FSome fear Orban could reject a result
OL,17,Foutright, but Chatham House's Roos
OL,18,Ftold ITV News he would "be careful in
OL,19,Fassuming he will do so."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G22/23
